</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1:&nbsp;</strong>Remove the cover from the adhesive part on one side of the strips.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 2:&nbsp;</strong>Apply the strips with the exposed adhesives to the back of your display.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 3:&nbsp;</strong>Remove the cover from the other side of the adhesives on the strips.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 4:&nbsp;</strong>Attach your display to the wall by pressing the areas with strips against it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 5:&nbsp;</strong>Grab the base of the display and gently pull it away from the wall.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 6:</strong>&nbsp;Unbind the command stips from each other and set the product aside.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 6:&nbsp;</strong>Allow the strips to bind to their respective surfaces for at least one hour.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 7:&nbsp;</strong>Attach your display back onto the surface by reattaching the strips.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Removal of Command Strips</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Command strips can be easily removed without leaving any residue behind. They lose adhesive property and are not reusable after you peel them off.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1:</strong>&nbsp;Grab the bottom corners of the display and pull away from the wall to detach.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 2:</strong>&nbsp;Pull the tab of the adhesive strips off the wall until they come off.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Installation With Suction Cup &amp; Hook</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This installation option is perfect for hanging your display from glass or other smooth surfaces.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1:</strong>&nbsp;Make sure the glass surface is smooth, clean and level.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 2:</strong>&nbsp;Stick the suction cups by pressing them to the application area.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 3:</strong>&nbsp;Hang the display by passing the hooks through the pre-drilled holes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Installation With Standoffs</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Get gold or silver colored standoffs for a classy wall mount. You&rsquo;ll need a screwdriver, drill, anchors, measuring tape, leveler and the standoffs with all included parts for the installation. You can get your product with pre-drilled holes from our menu.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1:&nbsp;</strong>Choose a flat level surface where you want to install the display.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 2:&nbsp;</strong>Mark the spots where you want to drill holes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 3:&nbsp;</strong>Drill holes on the marks and insert anchors.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 4:&nbsp;</strong>Screw the standoff barrels onto the anchors.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 5:&nbsp;</strong>Align the pre-drilled holes on the product with the standoff barrels.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 6:&nbsp;</strong>Slide the pre-drilled holes on the product over the barrels.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 7:&nbsp;</strong>Screw the standoff caps onto the barrels.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 8:</strong>&nbsp;The display should be firmly sandwiched between the barrels and the caps.</p>','<h1><strong>Specifications and Usage of Styrene Signs</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Thickness:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>0.020&quot;, 0.030&quot;, 0.060&quot;, 0.090&quot;, 0.125&quot;, 0.25&quot;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Installation:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Silver or gold standoffs, command strips, suction cup &amp; hook</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Weight:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>0.14lbs/sq ft, 0.19lbs/sq ft, 0.37lbs/sq ft, 0.56lbs/sq ft, 0.78lbs/sq ft, 1.56lbs/sq ft&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>(in order of thickness)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Printing Style:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Digital printing with UV inks</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Min Size:</strong></p>\r\