strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>We offer the following three cutting options for our corrugated signs:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Square / Rectangle Cut - cut with 90 degree edges</li>\r\n	<li>Outline Cut - cut in the exact shape of your design</li>\r\n	<li>Overline Cut - cut in the shape of your design with a white border</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Popular Applications for Coroplast Signs</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" height=\"540\" src=\"https://dash.brandexperts.ae/media/uploads/2025/03/01/corrugated-plastic-signs-for-real-estate.jpg\" width=\"960\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Coroplast signs are a multipurpose medium used to attract the attention of passersby, be they on foot or in vehicles. They&rsquo;re versatile with a wide range of applications. The most common uses for these plastic signs include but are not limited to:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Promotional signs&nbsp;- These signs, similar to&nbsp;yard signs, are popular for displaying promotional messages. They capture the attention of passersby and reach a wide audience with vibrant graphics.</li>\r\n	<li>Informative signs - They can also be used to share any kind of information. Just like&nbsp;aluminum signs,&nbsp;they&rsquo;re a great medium for relaying instructions, business hours, directions and so on.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Avoid folding your&nbsp;corrugated signs&nbsp;when storing to prevent damage.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Corrugated Plastic Signs FAQ</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>What installation options are available?</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>We offer several installation options with H and spider stakes, command strips, grommets and zip ties. Check out our installation section for detailed instructions.&nbsp;Keep in mind that when you order these products in sizes greater than 48&rdquo;x48&rdquo;, the corrugated flutes will be horizontal and the product will no longer be compatible with stakes.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>What&rsquo;s the lifespan of coroplast signs?</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Under moderate conditions, these displays will serve outdoors for more than 3 years.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Can corrugated plastic signs withstand heat?</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Corrugated plastic signs can withstand heat as well as snow, hail, heavy rain and freezing temperatures.</p>','<h1><strong>Installation Options for Corrugated Plastic Signs</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<p>We offer five different accessories for the installation of this product. It can be mounted on stakes or hung using zip ties, grommets and command strips.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Installation With H-Stakes:</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>H-stake signs are ideal for windy weather as they get firmly rooted in the ground. Choose an area with soft dirt to insert the stake without the need for additional tools.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1:</strong>&nbsp;Mark the place on the ground where you want to position the sign.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 2:&nbsp;</strong>Draw the two wires through the corrugated flutes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 3:</strong>&nbsp;Fix the bottom of the sign into the ground.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Installation With Spider Stakes:</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Check the firmness of the soil and choose ground that&rsquo;s not too hard or too brittle. The poles should easily press into soft dirt without the need for any additional tools.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1:&nbsp;</strong>Find a flat surface for the stake installation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 2:&nbsp;</strong>Carefully&nbsp;slide the sign onto the stake.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 3:</strong>&nbsp;Push the bottom of the spider stake into the soil.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Installation With Grommets:</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>We offer grommets for hanging installation. We&rsquo;ll fix the grommets onto the corners of the sign to streamline the process for you. You can insert zip ties, bungees, nylon ropes, hanging clips or any other hardware you prefer through the grommet holes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1:</strong>&nbsp;Take your sign with the pre-fixed grommets.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 2:</strong>&nbsp;Pass the hanging hardware of your choice through each grommet hole.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 3:</strong>&nbsp;Pass the hardware through the target location.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 4:</strong>&nbsp;Fix it firmly into place per hardware requirements.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Installation With Zip Ties:</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>You may also use zip ties to hang up your corrugated displays. Choose the grommet option for a clean look or pierce holes into the sign as you see fit. Make sure to leave enough space around the edges to prevent the material from ripping or cracking.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1:</strong>&nbsp;Make sure that the application surface is level.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 2:&nbsp;</strong>Pass the zip ties through the holes on the sign.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 3:</strong>&nbsp;Fasten the sign to the target location.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 4:&nbsp;</strong>Secure the zip ties.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 5:</strong>&nbsp;Cut the extra parts of the ties for a neater look.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Installation With Command Strips:</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This is the best accessory for hanging your sign from the wall without any visible installation hardware.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1:</strong>&nbsp;Clean the surface before attaching the sign to it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 2:</strong>&nbsp;Peel off the strip backing from one side to adhere it to the sign.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 3:</strong>&nbsp;Make sure the strips are firmly attached to the sign.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong>: Peel off the protective backing to apply the sign to the wall.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 5:</strong>&nbsp;Detach the sign from the wall by holding it from the bottom corners.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 6:</strong>&nbsp;Wait for at least an hour for the command strips to adhere to the wall.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 7:</strong>&nbsp;Apply the sign back to the wall by reattaching the strips.</p>','<h1><strong>Specifications for Corrugated Plastic Signs</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Thickness</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>0.16&rdquo;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Printing Options</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Single or double-sided printing</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Materials</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Coroplast</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Cutting Options</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Standard, overline or outline</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Min Size</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>4&quot;x4&quot;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Installation Accessories</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Grommets, zip ties, command strips</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Max Size</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>48&quot;x96&quot;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>H Stake</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Small - 0.15&quot;Tx10&quot;Wx15&quot;H, Big - 0.15&quot;Tx10&quot;Wx30&quot;H</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Common Sizes</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>12&quot;x6&quot;, 24&quot;x18&quot;, 24&quot;x24&quot;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Spider Stake</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>0.6&quot;Tx8&quot;Wx26&quot;H</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Color</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>White</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Lifespan (Indoors/Outdoors)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>5+ / 3+ years</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>',48.00,96.00,4.00,4.00,NULL,0,0,22.556188,0.1