be outdated. To check the current prices and discounts for this product, please refer to the calculator at the top of the page.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Econo Feather Flag FAQ</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>How long can I use my econo feather flag?</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>An econo feather flag lasts at least two years with proper maintenance. To extend its lifespan, keep the product away from direct sunlight and strong winds.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Is the econo feather flag fire resistant?</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The polyester face of the product is slow to ignite but will melt when in direct or close contact with fire. Keep the product away from flames and extreme heat to prevent damage and hazards.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>','<h1><strong>Installation of Econo Feather Flags</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<p>You’ll get the product in a standard package box. It’ll take about 5 minutes to assemble the construction.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Carefully remove all the pieces from the bag.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Connect the 4 rods together by sliding them into the slots in order.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 3:</strong> Start with the 2 long bottom rods and connect them to the medium middle rod.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 4:</strong> Attach the smallest top rod with a little knob on it to the others to finish.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 5:</strong> Slide the assembled pole set through the pole pocket on the face material.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 6:</strong> Pull the bungee cord at the base of the pole through the face loop.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 7:</strong> Pass the tip of the bungee cord through the metal clip on the bottom of the pole.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 8: </strong>Tie and knot the bungee cord tightly to secure the face to the pole.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 9:</strong> Find a level ground and hammer the ground stake deep into the soil.</