, follow the detailed steps.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>How to clean perforated window graphics?</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Get a soft towel, wet it lightly, and run it smoothly over the perforated window signs to clean them. Avoid using ammonia or acid-based cleaners as they may damage the ink.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Where to store the perforated window graphics?</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Keep perforated window graphics at +70°F and 50% humidity to preserve the quality of the product. The storage life of perforated window decals is one year.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Do you ship across the US and Canada?</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Yes, we do. Check our <a href=\"https://www.squaresigns.com/terms-and-policies/\">terms and policies page</a> to see if the perforated window decal qualifies for special offers or shipping discounts.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>reviews</h2>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>','<h1><strong>Installation Guide For Perforated Window Decals</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Dry Mounting</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is the quickest and easiest method for the installation of these products. However, it’s advisable to do the installation with assistance. It may be difficult to apply larger sizes alone and you won’t be able to reposition the adhesive once it sticks to the surface.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Clean the window before applying the product for a smooth installation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 2: </strong>Place the window perf on the glass in the position you want it to be applied.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 3:</strong> Fix it with tapes to keep the product in its place for a precise application.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 4:</strong> Remove part of the backing paper and apply the exposed section.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 5: </strong>Remove the rest of the backing paper and apply the remaining part of the sticker.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 6: </strong>Use a squeegee or a plastic card to remove any air bubbles.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 7:</strong> Work your way from the center to the edges to smooth out the adhesive.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 8: </strong>Use a razor blade to cut off any leftover edges if needed.</p>','<h1><strong>Specifications and Usage of Perforated Window Decals</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Opacity/Perforation:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>70/30</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Adhesiveness:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>One-sided</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Vinyl/Glue Thickness: </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>6mil/1mil</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Printing:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>One-sided with full color UV inks</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Weight:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>0.08lbs/sq ft</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Min Size:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>6”x6”</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Pierce Diameter:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>1.5mm</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Max Size:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>52”x1,680”</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Finish:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Glossy</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Common Sizes:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>15”x36”, 20”x41”, 48”x96”, etc.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Color:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>White frontside, black backside</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Visibility:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>One-way</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Application Temperature:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>+40°F</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Installation:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>