egislation and regulations, so you’ll need to check them before applying a car window decal to your car. Even if they are legal in your location, make sure the graphics don’t impair the driver’s view, don’t contain harassment and don’t distract other drivers. Note: We don’t bear any responsibility for the misuse of our product.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong><strong>What types of car window graphics do you offer?</strong></strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>We offer transparent, obscured and perf finishes for our windshield decals, each for different purposes. You can read their detailed descriptions in the first section of this page and choose the best fit for you in our tool. We also offer sticky letter displays as a distinct product.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong><strong>Are graphics for vehicle windows safe?</strong></strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>The product is safe with proper use. The misuse of removable car window decals may have safety risks. Be sure that they don’t block the driver’s view. The variant with clear finish or one-way visibility is better for your back and front windshield decal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Reflective car decals are a good option if you want to make your message visible at night. Be careful with reflective graphics for your car window decal as they might be dangerous to other drivers. Use them in smaller sizes and always check with your local and state regulations regarding its legality.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong><strong>Can I use this product on all of my vehicle’s windows?</strong></strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Car back window decals are the most popular among drivers. However, you can consider other areas of application for this medium. Side windows and the front windshield can be used as well, provided that you follow legal regulations and safety guidelines.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong><strong>How to apply decals to car windows?</strong></strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>There are two methods to apply car back window decals or any other kind of adhesive graphics to the windshield. Dry mounting is quicker while wet mounting allows you to reposition the product during installation. Please remember that wet mounting only works for clear products. You can read the installation page for more information.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong><strong>How to remove decals from car windows?</strong></strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Peel a corner of the material and pull away the rest for an easy removal. Alternatively, You may spray rubbing alcohol onto the custom car window decals until they’re wet and wait a few minutes. The wrinkled graphics should be simple to remove. Use a plastic scrape or other tool that won’t damage the glass.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong><strong>Do you offer shipping?</strong></strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Order from <a href=\"https://www.brandexperts.ae\">Brand Experts</a> to get your vehicle window decals delivered across the UAE . Check our <a href=\"https://www.brandexperts.ae/\">terms and policies page</a> to see if this product qualifies for special offers or shipping discounts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>','<h1><strong>Installation Of Car Window Decals</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Dry Mounting</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is the quickest method to install this product. Ask for assistance in case of large options to make application easier. You won’t be able to reposition them after application.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Clean the car window before applying the product.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Position and place the product on the window.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 3: </strong>Fix it with tape to keep it in place for precise application.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 4: </strong>Remove part of the backing paper and apply the exposed section.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 5:</strong> Remove the rest of the backing paper and apply the product.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 6:</strong> Get rid of air bubbles with a squeegee or plastic card.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Wet Mounting</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The wet mounting method provides the most accurate results. This method is only applicable for clear products.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Clean the area of application.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Spray the surface with soap water to help you reposition the item if needed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 3:</strong> Take the backing paper and spray soap water onto the sticky side.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 4:</strong> Apply the medium to the vehicle and reposition by sliding it if needed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 5: </strong>Flatten it out with a squeegee or a plastic card to get rid of air bubbles.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 6:</strong> Start from the middle and work your way out towards the edges.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 7: </strong>Once you’re satisfied, use a dry cloth to get rid of excess water.</p>','<h1><strong>Specifications And Usage Of Car Window Decals</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Thickness:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>4 mil / 6.3 mil (opaque, clear / perforated)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Material Finish:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Glossy with matte printing</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Min Size:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>6”x6”</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Application Options:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Standard, inside glass</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Max Size:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>52”x1,680”</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Cutting Options:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Standard, outline, overline, rounded</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Common Sizes:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>12\"x6\", 12\"x18\", 18\"x24\", 24\"x36\", 48\"x72\", custom</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Install