r\n<h4><strong>Will the driver be able to see through the perforated car window decal?</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>We use a 70% print to 30% perforation ratio that provides one-way transparency. It means your advertisement will be seen by passersby while maintaining clear visibility and safety for the driver.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Do the punctures on perforated rear window decals decrease vibrancy?</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Our product is UV-printed over evenly pierced micro-holes. The content on it will be vibrant as well as fade-resistant for at least three years.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Do see-through car window decals scratch or leave residue on glass?</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>No, the adhesives don’t leave any residue, stains or scratches. All you have to do is wipe with a moist cloth to restore the gloss.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>How do you care for a perforated car window decal?</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Don’t power-wash the vinyl to assure it doesn’t come off. Avoid using abrasive washing brushes to prevent scratching and tearing the material. The best way to clean it is with a soft, wet cloth to remove dirt and dust from the holes.</p>','<h1><strong>Installation of Perforated Car Window Decals</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Dry Mounting</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is the quickest method to install a perforated car window decal. But ask for help because it will be difficult to apply it alone, as you won’t be able to reposition the decal if needed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1</strong>: Clean the car window before applying the decal for a smooth installation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 2</strong>: Take the decal and place it on the window.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 3</strong>: Fix it with tapes which will keep the decal secure in place for precise application.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 4</strong>: Remove part of the backing paper and apply the decal by flattening it with a squeegee or a plastic card.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 5</strong>: When you’re done with that section remove the rest of the backing paper and apply the decal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 6</strong>: Make sure to get rid of all the bubbles by smoothing them out with a tool or your hand.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 7</strong>: When it\'s done, use a razor blade to cut the extra edges of the perforated car window decal.</p>','<h1><strong>Specifications of Perforated Car Window Decals</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Thickness:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>6.3mil</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Installation:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Dry mounting with a squeegee</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Weight:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>0.08lbs/sqft</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Printing:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Digital, high resolution, full-color printing with UV inks</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Min/max size:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>6\"x6\"/52\"x1680\"</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Usage:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>3+ years depending on weather conditions</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Common sizes:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>24”x24”, 53\"x14\" 60\"x17”, 66\"x20\", 66\"x29\" </p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Perforated pattern:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>70/30 (70% print to 30% perforation)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>',1680.00,52.00,6.00,6.00,NULL,0,0,44.753897,0.140145,NULL),(63,'Reflective Car Decals','Visible day and night, reflective car decals are perfect for spreading all kinds of messages that get noticed fast.','https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcTJ_tR9w0YE-v20LACs8kegkWm__J5XU254Kg&s','https://dejpknyizje2n.cloudfront.net/media/carstickers/versions/reflective-st