rt of the backing paper and adhere the exposed section.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 4:</strong> Remove the rest of the backing and adhere the remaining part of the sticker.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 5:</strong> Use a squeegee or plastic card to remove any air bubbles.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 6:</strong> Work your way from top to bottom and center to sides to smooth out the material.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Installation by Wet Mounting</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This method allows you to reposition the product during the installation process if needed. It’s only applicable for clear products.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Wash and dry the glass to get rid of any dust and debris.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Spray dish soap water on the application area to help reposition the product if needed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 3:</strong> Remove the backing paper and spray dish soap water on the sticky side of the product.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 4:</strong> Apply the adhesive to the wet glass, starting from the top and moving down.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 5:</strong> Use a squeegee or plastic card to remove any water and air bubbles. </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 6:</strong> Work your way from the center to the edges to smooth out the material.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 7:</strong> Use a soft cloth to dry off the remaining water for a final application.</p>','<h1><strong>Specifications and Usage of Truck Window Decals</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Thicknesses:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>4 mil (clear & opaque)</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>6.3 mil (perforated)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Material Finish:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clear, opaque, perforated</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Min Size:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>6”x6”</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Application Options:</strong