n			<td>\r\n			<p>48&quot;x24&quot;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>$ 126.32/248.27</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>48&quot;x18&quot;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>$ 107.97/209.33</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>24&quot;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>$ 101.40/175.90</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>24&quot;x24&quot;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>$ 89.62/170.39</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>72&quot;x48&quot;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>$ 273.07/559.77</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>72&quot;x24&quot;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>$ 163․00/326.14</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>48&quot;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>$ 226.80/419.90</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>48&quot;x48&quot;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>$ 199.69/404.02</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>*Please note that the prices listed don&rsquo;t include drilled holes, mounting accessories or advanced cutting options. Additionally, the prices in this chart may be outdated. For accurate pricing and available discounts, please use the calculator at the top of the page.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Material and Printing Options for Acrylic Prints</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>We create custom acrylic photo prints by mirror-printing your picture directly onto the back surface of clear acrylic. The photo is visible in the right orientation from the other side. The optically clear sheet of the material adds depth and brilliance to your pictures on acrylic.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Second surface acrylic photo printing offers protection against scratches and damages to your print on plexiglass. Although the printing process turns the surface texture matte, the front-facing side retains a glossy appearance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We use the highest-quality printers available paired with UV-stable inks for acrylic photo printing that&rsquo;s as stunning as it gets.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Acrylic Photo Prints With Different Edge Options</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" height=\"610\" src=\"/media/uploads/2025/03/01/acrylic-prints-cutting-options.jpg\" width=\"1084\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>We offer multiple edge options for our custom acrylic prints that you can select before placing an order. Acrylic photo cutting styles allow you to further personalize your prints and add a final stylistic touch to your decor.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Acrylic Prints With a Halo Effect / Overline Cut</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>We offer overline cutting known for its &ldquo;halo effect&rdquo; for custom acrylic prints. This option adds clear edges to the border of your pictures on acrylic. The technique creates a unique frame around your print, priming it for home decor or gallery displays. Mostly used for photography exhibitions, this style will impart a museum-worthy appearance to your custom acrylic photo prints. Keep in mind that the size you select for your photo will include a &frac14; - &frac12; inch clear edge. Contact us for custom-sized edges.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you&rsquo;d like to have acrylic prints with a colored frame, gradients, or anything other than clear, include it in the design and choose one of the other cutting options to ensure your product doesn&rsquo;t feature a clear edge.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Square or Rectangle Cuts</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>This standard cutting option for acrylic glass photo prints is the most popular choice for our customers. Choosing this one, you&rsquo;ll get a print that has 90&deg; corners with sharp edges.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Rounded Cut</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>As with the standard-cut option, you&rsquo;ll still get 90&deg; corners but the edges will be rounded at 1&rdquo;, &frac34;&rdquo; (0.75), and &frac12;&rdquo; (0.5) radius, depending on the size of your acrylic picture prints. This option will give your decor a softer look.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Outline Cutting</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>We offer full customization when we print a photo on acrylic glass so you can get decor in any shape you can imagine. All you need to do is design your acrylic pictures with a custom outline and we&rsquo;ll make precision-cuts to match.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Circle / Oval Cut</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Upload your pictures and choose this option if you need round acrylic prints. Get the perfect circular or oval shape by selecting the height and width of your design. Make sure no important part of the image is cut off by examining the proof we send you before production.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Installation Of Acrylic Photo Prints</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Acrylic printing can be installed in several ways such as direct-mounting, hanging, or as free-standing displays. We offer the following installation accessories for mounting your acrylic prints.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>How To Install Acrylic Decor With Standoffs</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Your acrylic photo prints, especially large-scale ones, may be mounted using standoffs for an extra secure installation. Acrylic prints mounted this way can be applied to interior and exterior walls. For installation, you will need a screwdriver, drill, anchors, and standoffs with all included parts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1:</strong>&nbsp;Use the drilled holes in the product as a reference to mark the spots on the wall.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 2:</strong>&nbsp;Drill the holes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 3:</strong>&nbsp;Force the anchor into the hole, place the spacer on the wall, and screw it in place.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 4:</strong>&nbsp;Align the drilled hole of the acrylic photo print with the hole of the spacer.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 5:</strong>&nbsp;Screw the cap into the hole to dead-fix the material.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 6:</strong>&nbsp;Repeat the process for as many holes as there are.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>How To Install Acrylic Photo Prints With Command Strips</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>We recommend using these accessories with opaque or fully-printed materials only.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1:</strong>&nbsp;Clean the application area with rubbing alcohol.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 2:</strong>&nbsp;Separate the strips and click them together.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 3:</strong>&nbsp;Peel the backing paper off the adhesive part of one of the strips.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 4:</strong>&nbsp;Adhere the exposed backing of the strips to the back of your product.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 5:</strong>&nbsp;Peel the backing paper off the other side of the command strips.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 6:</strong>&nbsp;Firmly press the adhesive backs of the command strips to the wall.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 7:</strong>&nbsp;Ensure that your product is firmly fastened to the application area.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>How To Install Acrylic Displays With Easel Backs</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Easel backs can be used to display small-scale custom acrylic prints on flat surfaces like tables and countertops.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1:</strong>&nbsp;Fold the wing of the easel back to open the pre-dotted area.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 2:</strong>&nbsp;Fold down the circular easel stabilizer to secure the wing in its slot.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 3:</strong>&nbsp;Remove the tape from the adhesive parts of the easel back.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 4:</strong>&nbsp;Fix the easel back to the back of your product.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 5:</strong>&nbsp;Press it for a few seconds to make sure it&rsquo;s firmly bound.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Comparison of Acrylic Photo Prints with Similar Products</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>This chart includes a comparison of custom acrylic prints and similar products. Please note that the prices don&rsquo;t include any accessories or mounting systems. They&rsquo;re listed for the default thickness, color, cutting, and printing options that differ from product to product.</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n