n\r\n<p>Photographic Metal Prints<br />\r\nMetal Photo Prints for Your Home</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/media/uploads/2025/03/01/custom-metal-print-for-home.jpg\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Metal print of a cheerful family of four pictured outdoors, mounted on the wall<br />\r\nIf you want to strike awe in anyone who sets foot into your home, look no further. These metal wall prints are showstoppers. Aluminum photo prints will instantly capture the attention of anyone who walks past them. The high-definition images create a unique focal point with an ultra-modern appeal. Showcasing photos on metal has a striking effect. You can use them to display everything from family portraits and scenic landscapes to classical works of art. The graphics look bold and substantive, attributes people associate with class and cultivation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Metal Picture Prints for Your Office</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" height=\"540\" src=\"/media/uploads/2025/03/01/custom-metal-prints-for-office-interior.jpg\" width=\"960\" /><br />\r\nLarge metal print showcasing a rainforest and waterfall in an office conference room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Stunning aluminum prints of photography will have an awesome effect on your work environment. Whether you hang up aluminum picture prints of your products or majestic scenery, customers and staff will appreciate them. Greet everyone with tasteful photos on metal and leave a strong first impression. A thoughtful custom aluminum photo print will build trust among your clientele. Metal photo prints indicate the refinement with which you carry out your daily operations. Incorporate them into your interior branding and showcase how serious you are about your work.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Metal Prints for Art Galleries</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/media/uploads/2025/03/01/custom-metal-print-for-art-gallery_q3qZjKe.jpg\" /><br />\r\nMetal print of a matte finish showcasing a landscape painting featuring a floral field</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Artists, photographers, and businessmen can all display their selected images in galleries and showrooms. The product works wonders whether it&rsquo;s for the sake of selling a product or showing off the art you&rsquo;ve created. The go-to material for displaying a masterpiece should be a masterpiece in and of itself. No other medium will do justice to great pieces better than metal prints. The bold, formidable aluminum sheets will have people fascinated at worst and writing you checks at best.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Custom Metal Prints for Public Spaces</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"Large metal print of breakfast food in a restaurant featuring a quote in green and black\" src=\"https://cdn.squaresigns.com/images/media/custom-metal-print-for-restaurant.jpg\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Large metal print of breakfast food in a restaurant featuring a quote in green and black<br />\r\nIncorporate metal prints indoors to transform your space and elevate your branding. These sleek and contemporary designs not only enhance the aesthetic appeal of your interiors but also create a welcoming atmosphere for customers and employees alike. Incorporate playful tongue-in-cheek sayings, motivational quotes, or custom imagery that aligns with your brand identity to foster a positive and memorable experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Metal Prints by Material<br />\r\nStandard Aluminum</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Aluminum is a highly durable, corrosion-resistant, and eco-friendly material. Our standard product comes in 0.040&rdquo; thick sheets with a white coat. The coating offers a perfect backdrop for high-contrast colors, making it well-suited for displaying metal photo prints with vibrant graphics. Aluminum signs render any design exquisite thanks to their unique appearance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dibond</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dibond is a more advanced type of composite aluminum. It&rsquo;s made of two aluminum layers with a plastic core in between. A regular sheet of this material is 0.125&rdquo; thick but the material is lighter and more resilient than standard aluminum. Metal photo prints made of this material or any other dibond sign last for several years.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Custom Metal Prints by Size<br />\r\nWe have metal prints available in sizes ranging from 4&rdquo;x4&rdquo; up to 48&rdquo;x96&rdquo;. You can also request your metal prints in custom cuts. Below, you can find some of the most popular sizes for metal prints along with their base prices:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nStandard Aluminum</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dibond</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Size</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Price</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Price</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4&rdquo;x4&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$17.62</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$16.02</p>\r\n\r\n<p>12&rdquo;x12&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$26.5</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$24.09</p>\r\n\r\n<p>12&rdquo;x24&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$36.5</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$33.18</p>\r\n\r\n<p>24&rdquo;x24&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$56.49</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$51.36</p>\r\n\r\n<p>12&rdquo;x36&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$46.05</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$42.27</p>\r\n\r\n<p>24&rdquo;x36&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$76.49</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$69.53</p>\r\n\r\n<p>48&rdquo;x96&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$336.39</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$305.81</p>\r\n\r\n<p>* The prices in this chart may be outdated. To check the current prices and discounts for this product, please refer to the calculator at the top of the page.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Printing Photos on Metal<br />\r\nOrder your custom metal prints displaying all kinds of graphics or photos. Photo printing on metal is similar to other products. Our digital printers apply UV inks onto the material coated in white, while simultaneously drying the inks with a UV curing system. This makes the inks fade- and sun-resistant so that your metal prints will retain their vivid colors for a long time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Metal Prints by Shape<br />\r\nWe offer our metal picture prints in several shapes. We have four main cutting options for metal prints, the most popular of which are rectangular and square cuts. Choose any of the options you prefer to create your unique custom metal prints.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Square/Rectangle Cut<br />\r\nThis cutting option means that your metal prints will be cut in a regular square or rectangle shape with sharp corners.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Rounded Cut<br />\r\nThis is similar to square or rectangular cut metal prints but with rounded corners to provide a smoother shape.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Outline Cut<br />\r\nWith this cutting option, your aluminum art prints will be cut in the exact shape of their design and without any additional space around them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Overline Cut<br />\r\nThe overline cutting option will give you an aluminum print cut into the shape of your exact design with a thin border running around it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Custom Metal Prints by Mounting<br />\r\nThere are two main ways to hang aluminum photo prints that will make your graphics stand out. You can find the mounting options below and a detailed guide on how to put up the metal prints in the installation section.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Standoff Mounting</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hanging up your custom metal photo prints with the help of metallic standoffs gives them a polished look. You can order from two to six drilled holes for the product, choosing among different standoff options.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>*Please note that you should select the drilled holes and standoff options from the design tool before finalizing your order.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Command Strip Mounting</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you prefer a clean hanging method for your metal prints without anything obstructing the actual design, command strips are the way to go. They&rsquo;re also a good choice if you intend to move your metal prints from one place to another. The command strips don&rsquo;t leave holes in the wall and are easy to remove.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Comparison of Metal Photo Prints and Similar Products<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nMetal photo prints</p>\r\n\r\n<p>PVC signs</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Acrylic photo prints</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Canvas prints</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;<br />\r\nWooden signs</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Brushed Aluminum Signs</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sizes (min/max)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4&quot;x4&quot;-48&quot;x96&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4&quot;x4&quot;-48&quot;x96&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4&quot;x4&quot;-48&quot;x96&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>8&quot;x8&quot;-48&quot;x96&quot; (with a frame)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1,740&quot;x120&quot; (without a frame)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>6&quot;x6&quot;-48&quot;x96&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4&rdquo;x4&rdquo; - 48&rdquo;x96&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;<br />\r\nPrice (min/max)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$16.20-305.81</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$17.26-211.36</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$53.95-346.44</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$44.54-413.31 (11,951.63)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$77.78-377.60</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$27.00 - $546.19</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lifespan (indoor/outdoor)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>15+/10+ years</p>\r\n\r\n<p>10+/3+ years</p>\r\n\r\n<p>15+/5+ years</p>\r\n\r\n<p>60+ years/ N/A</p>\r\n\r\n<p>7+/1+ years</p>\r\n\r\n<p>10+/5+ years</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Printing Options</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Standard</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Standard,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Double-sided</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Standard, Second-surface</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Standard</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Standard,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Double-sided</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Standard</p>\r\n\r\n<p>* The prices in this chart may be outdated. To check the current prices and discounts for this product, please refer to the calculator at the top of the page.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Metal Photo Prints FAQs<br />\r\nWhat are metal photo prints?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Metal photo prints are photos printed on sheets of standard aluminum or dibond. They create an elegant and professional effect for the images on display. Print whatever photo you wish on the medium, getting them in any size you need. You can also choose advanced cutting techniques and mounting options in our design platform.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What are custom metal prints with artwork?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Aluminum art prints are pieces of artwork that have been printed on sheets of metal. These differ from photos on metal as they showcase artistic images like paintings, designs, and original works created by an artist. The metal sheet gives them a unique, contemporary appeal. The product provides gallery-quality images suitable for decor and exhibitions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What&rsquo;s the difference between standard aluminum and dibond for metal photo prints?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Standard aluminum is a single sheet with a thickness of 0.040&rdquo;, making it a thinner and more lightweight option. Dibond, on the other hand, consists of a plastic core sandwiched between two thin aluminum layers, with a thickness of 0.125&rdquo;. It offers greater durability, making it less susceptible to damage from impacts or bending.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Can I order metal prints online?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Yes, you can create and order your metal prints online through our website. Set the size and material, choose a cutting option, and specify your mounting accessories. You can upload your photos or any available design you find for metal prints online. We&rsquo;ll have it shipped the next day anywhere across the UAE.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>How are metal prints hung?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Metal Prints can be hung using one of two methods. You can put them up with metal standoffs or with command strips depending on your requirements. Standoffs can hold larger sizes with a polished appearance. Command strips go invisible on the back of the medium and don&rsquo;t require any holes to be drilled into the wall. See our installation section for details.</p>','<h1><strong>Installation Guide For Metal Photo Prints</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Installation With Standoffs</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Standoffs are one of the most secure forms of installation for this product as they are on the heavier side, especially when large-scale.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1:&nbsp;</strong>Determine the location where the sign should be installed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 2:</strong>&nbsp;Drill holes into the wall that are aligned with the pre-drilled holes of the metal sign.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 3:&nbsp;</strong>Insert anchors into the holes and screw the barrels of the standoffs into place.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 4:&nbsp;</strong>Place the pre-drilled holes of the metal photo print against the barrels on the wall.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 5:</strong>&nbsp;Screw in the caps of the standoffs to sandwich the print between the barrels and the caps.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Installation With Command Strips</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Use as many strips as required for the secure installation of the photo print in your selected size.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1:&nbsp;</strong>Make sure the application surface is smooth and clean.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 2:</strong>&nbsp;Take the strips and remove the backing liners from one side.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 3:</strong>&nbsp;Position them on the back of the photo print.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 4:</strong>&nbsp;Press the fasteners to make sure the strips are firmly attached to the print.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 5:</strong>&nbsp;Remove the backing liners on the other side of the strips</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 6:</strong>&nbsp;Apply the metal photo print to evenly marked points on the wall.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 7:</strong>&nbsp;Hold the photo from the bottom and pull to detach it from the back strips.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 8:</strong>&nbsp;Wait for at least an hour to make sure the back strips are firmly attached to the wall.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 9:</strong>&nbsp;Mount the print back onto the wall by reattaching the print and wall strips together.</p>','<h1><strong>Specifications Of Metal Photo Prints</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Materials:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Standard aluminum, dibond</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Thicknesses:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>0.040&rdquo;, 0.125&rdquo;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Min Size:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>4&rdquo;x4&rsquo;&rsquo;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n	