rinting options to personalize your designs. The single-sided printing is available in clear, opaque, gold, and frosted finishes, while double-sided printing is offered only for the black opaque option.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nStandard printing involves applying the graphics directly onto the material, resulting in a matte finish&mdash;ideal for opaque pieces. Second-surface printing, on the other hand, is a reverse printing method that preserves the glossy surface of transparent items. The design is printed on the back, making it visible from the front, and is only available for the clear acrylic material.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/media/uploads/2025/03/03/acrylic-sign-material.jpg\" style=\"height:375px; width:500px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Material of Acrylic Signs</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>If you&#39;ve decided on purchasing acrylic signs, it&#39;s important to learn about their features and variations to select the one that suits your needs best. The products offer excellent image protection and impressive longevity, particularly indoors. When used outdoors, acrylic signs are still highly resistant to direct sunlight, thanks to our UV inks.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThese products are available in transparent, opaque, and reflective options, and boast exceptional durability. The material is impact- and moisture-resistant, weighing half as much as glass. With 92% light transmission, it&rsquo;s also more shatter-resistant than glass, being 17 times stronger. You can choose between three thicknesses: ⅛&rdquo; (all), &frac14;&rdquo; (clear, white, black, frosted), and ⅜&rdquo; (clear).</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Setup Of Acrylic Signs</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Acrylic signs can be set up in several ways using different accessories.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>How to Install Acrylic Signs With Standoffs</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/media/uploads/2025/03/03/install-with-standoffs-step-1.jpg\" style=\"height:375px; width:500px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Step 1:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mark the spots on the application area using the drilled holes in your signs as a reference.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/media/uploads/2025/03/03/install-with-standoffs-step-2.jpg\" style=\"height:375px; width:500px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Step 2:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Drill the holes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/media/uploads/2025/03/03/install-with-standoffs-step-3.jpg\" style=\"height:375px; width:500px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Step 3:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Force the anchor into the hole. Place the spacer on the wall and screw it in place.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/media/uploads/2025/03/03/install-with-standoffs-step-4.jpg\" style=\"height:375px; width:500px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Step 4:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Align the drilled hole of the material with the hole of the spacer.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/media/uploads/2025/03/03/install-with-standoffs-step-5_5j7VHUM.jpg\" style=\"height:375px; width:500px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Step 5:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Screw the cap into the hole to dead-fix the material.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/media/uploads/2025/03/03/install-with-standoffs-step-6.jpg\" style=\"height:375px; width:500px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Step 6:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Repeat the process for as many holes as there are.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><em>*Please note that you should select the drilled holes and standoff options from the design tool before finalizing your order.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>How to Install Acrylic Signs With Command Strips</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/media/uploads/2025/03/03/install-with-command-strips-step-1.jpg\" style=\"height:375px; width:500px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Step 1:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Clean the application area with rubbing alcohol.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/media/uploads/2025/03/03/install-with-command-strips-step-2.jpg\" style=\"height:375px; width:500px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Step 2:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Separate the pair of command strips.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/media/uploads/2025/03/03/install-with-command-strips-step-3.jpg\" style=\"height:375px; width:500px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Step 3:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Attach the velcro faces of the separated strips to each other.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/media/uploads/2025/03/03/install-with-command-strips-step-4.jpg\" style=\"height:375px; width:500px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Step 4:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Peel off the backing paper off the adhesive part of one of the strips.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/media/uploads/2025/03/03/install-with-command-strips-step-5.jpg\" style=\"height:375px; width:500px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Step 5:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Adhere the exposed backing of the strips to the back of your product.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/media/uploads/2025/03/03/install-with-command-strips-step-6.jpg\" style=\"height:375px; width:500px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Step 6:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Press firmly on the back of the command strips to bind them to the product.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/media/uploads/2025/03/03/install-with-command-strips-step-7.jpg\" style=\"height:375px; width:500px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Step 7:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Peel off the protective backing off the other command strips.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/media/uploads/2025/03/03/install-with-command-strips-step-8.jpg\" style=\"height:375px; width:500px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Step 8:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Attach your sign to the wall by pressing firmly on the product for at least 30 seconds.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><em>*We recommend using these accessories with opaque or fully-printed materials only.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>How to Install Acrylic Signs With Easel Backs</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/media/uploads/2025/03/03/install-with-easel-backs-step-1.jpg\" style=\"height:375px; width:500px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Step 1:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Fold the wing of the easel back to open the pre-dotted area.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/media/uploads/2025/03/03/install-with-easel-backs-step-2.jpg\" style=\"height:375px; width:500px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Step 2:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Fold down the circular easel stabilizer to secure the wing 