\n<p>Spray window cleaner on the material and use a razor blade to chip away at the adhesive. Then slowly pull the medium upwards and peel it off. Removable window decals&nbsp;don&rsquo;t leave any glue or residue on the glass. Clean the area with a glass cleaner or lukewarm water once you&rsquo;ve removed the graphics. Now you&rsquo;re done.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>How can I clean my custom window decal?</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Clear off your vinyl window decal regularly with a feather duster. Then spray glass cleaner on the adhesive that doesn&rsquo;t contain ammonia, alcohol or other harsh chemicals. Wipe it with a soft, cotton towel. Dry around the edges of the medium carefully to prevent excess moisture. Excess moisture can cause the corners of the product to peel off with time.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Where can I store my custom window decal?</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Roll up your adhesive graphics with the protective backing paper on them to avoid spoiling the glue on the backside. Keep them in a dry, dark place. Don&rsquo;t store other items on your adhesives.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Is a custom window decal reusable?</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Vinyl window decals are made for one-time uses. They&rsquo;ll serve for more than three years preserving the graphics&rsquo; vibrancy and fresh look. However, you won&#39;t be able to reuse the adhesives once you&#39;ve removed them. Use&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.squaresigns.com/product/static-clings/\">static clings</a>&nbsp;instead. They&rsquo;re both reusable and can withstand for more than three years.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>How to make a personalized window decal?</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Go to our online&nbsp;design platform&nbsp;and start creating your graphics from scratch. Add designer-made illustrations from the list as well as background colors, texts and icons. You can also upload your personal photos and design them to get personalized graphics for your custom window decal.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Where do you ship your products?</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>We ship all our products anywhere you want within the UAE.&nbsp;Check our&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.brandexperts.ae/\">terms and policies page</a>&nbsp;to see if this product qualifies for special offers or shipping discounts.</p>','<h1><strong>Installation Of Window Decals</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Installation by Dry Mounting</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is the quickest method for applying smaller-sized adhesives that are easy to position.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1:</strong>&nbsp;Clean the window before applying the product.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 2:</strong>&nbsp;Place the window adhesive in the correct position.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 3:</strong>&nbsp;Fix the product with tape at the top center to keep it in place.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 4:</strong>&nbsp;Remove one part of the backing paper and adhere the exposed section.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 5:</strong>&nbsp;Remove the rest of the backing paper and adhere the remaining part of the graphics.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 6:</strong>&nbsp;Use a squeegee or plastic card to remove any air bubbles from under the graphics.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 7:</strong>&nbsp;Work your way from the center to the edges to smooth out the adhesive.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Installation by Wet Mounting</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This method allows you to reposition the adhesive graphics during the installation process if needed. Bear in mind that this method is only applicable with clear products.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1:</strong>&nbsp;Wash and dry the window to get rid of any dust and debris.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 2:</strong>&nbsp;Spray dish soap water on the window to help reposition the product if needed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 3:</strong>&nbsp;Remove the backing paper and spray dish soap water on the adhesive side of the product.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 4:</strong>&nbsp;Apply it to the wet window, starting from the top and moving down.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 5:</strong>&nbsp;Use a squeegee or plastic card to force any water and air bubbles out from under the product.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 6:</strong>&nbsp;Work your way from the center to the edges to smooth out the display.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 7:</strong>&nbsp;Use a soft cloth to dry the excess water for a final application.</p>','<h1><strong>Specifications And Usage Of Window Decals</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Thicknesses:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>4 mil (clear &amp; opaque)</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>4.7 mil (frosted)</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>6.3 mil (perforated)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Material Finish:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Clear transparent</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Opaque white</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Frosted translucent</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>Perforated</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Min Size:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>6&rdquo;x6&rdquo;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Application Options:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Standard, inside-glass</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Max Size:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>58&rdquo;x1,680&rdquo; (clear, opaque, frosted)</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>52&rdquo;x1,680&rdquo; (perforated)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Cutting Options:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Standard, outline, overline, rounded</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Common Sizes:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>12&rdquo;x24&rdquo;, 18&rdquo;x24&rdquo;, 36&rdquo;x42&rdquo;, 36&rdquo;x36&rdquo;, 48&rdquo;x72&rdquo;, 48&rdquo; x 96&rdquo;, custom</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Installation Accessories:</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p>Squeegee</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Lifespan (Indoors)</strong></