inside of a clear glass with the design looking out whereas the opaque has a white coat which gets direct printing for front facing designs.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>How to make window clings?</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Make your own window clings with our&nbsp;sign design tool. Select the material finish that you want along with a unique style that suits your needs. Design your business, personal or holiday window clings&nbsp;with all the features on our platform including modifiable templates and creative icons.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>How do window clings work?</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>A custom window cling is a glue-free display that can be applied to glass. It functions based on the static electricity created between one side of the display and a glossy application surface. You can reposition the static window cling and it won&rsquo;t lose its adhesive properties.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>How to apply window clings?</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Clear the application area of any dust and debris. Remove the protector that covers the graphics on your static window cling and attach them to the application surface. Use a squeegee or a plastic card to smooth out the display, moving from from the center to the edges.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Do window clings go inside or outside?</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Our glass clings are suitable for both sides of any glass or similar veneer. You may use custom window clings with inside-glass graphics for transparent surfaces. This will prevent them coming loose or falling off because of heavy wind, rain, heat or snow when used outdoors.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>How to remove window clings?</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Removable window clings don&rsquo;t leave any residue or stains on the application surface after use. To take them off, all you have to do is pull a corner of the display with your fingernail and peel it away. Be careful to keep the material intact if you want to reuse it later.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>How to reuse window clings?</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Both white and clear window clings are reusable. Stick your custom window cling onto a wax paper to store it for later. The paper will keep the sticky side clean and protect its clinging strength. Remove the protective layer and reapply whenever you want to use it.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>How to clean window clings?</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Wipe the surface of your window clings using a dampened microfiber cloth if they&rsquo;re visibly dirty. Be careful to not peel them at the edges when cleaning.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>How to store window clings?</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>For storage, choose a dry, clean spot away from direct sunlight and moisture. Avoid getting dust on the product to preserve its clinging effect. Clings for windows can curl at the edges when laid out in storage for an extended period of time. To prevent this, place a book on top to keep them flat or roll them up fully depending on their size.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Where to buy window clings?</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>We deliver customized window clings to any location within the UAE.&nbsp;Check our&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.brandexperts.ae/\">terms and policies page</a>&nbsp;to see if this product qualifies for special offers or shipping discounts.</p>','<h1><strong>Installation Of Window Clings</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<p>These displays can be applied, removed and repositioned as often as needed. They&rsquo;re designed for dry application.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 1:</strong>&nbsp;Clean and dry the application surface until it&rsquo;s smooth and dust-free.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 2:</strong>&nbsp;Remove the protective layer of the graphics.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 3:</strong>&nbsp;Position and place the product on the application surface.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 4:</strong>&nbsp;Smooth it out with a squeegee or use a plastic card.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Step 5:</strong>&nbsp;Move the squeegee from the center to the edges to get rid of any air bubbles.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</